I think those that chaincast is hurting the class because instead of Verant looking for a viable fix for what is wrong with the class, they instead figure that we will work out a way around whatever problem that is in front of us.  While it is good and shows innovation that some Magicians have, we are letting Verant off the hook.  <br>
<br>
For example, our pets have a few hundred more Hitpoints then what they had in Kunark.  Yet every other pet classes hitpoints have went up considerably to almost equal our pets.  Our pets hitpoints shouldve atleast doubled in this expansion considering how much the Mobs now hit for.  Or they should be giving away to not absorb damage as much.  Verant knows how many hitpoints our pets have and how much the mobs hit for, yet they just raised the pet level and not really touched anything else.  Do they do that to the mobs?  No, they raise the levels, attack, hitpoints, etc.  Our pets should advance the same way with the expansions.<br>
<br>
But maybe they figure if we can chaincast, why raise the hitpoints.<br>
