<br>
Nice cop out with the 'chain casting wasn't originally intended and is therefore hurting the class.'<br>
<br>
You know what else 'wasn't originally intended?'<br>
<br>
Feign Death pulling.<br>
<br>
Quad kiting.<br>
<br>
I'm sure I could name more.<br>
<br>
I have no sympathy for you. You cry foul at mages wanting chain casting improvements, claiming they only want to improve on mages who chain cast, as if it were some competition of chain cast vs non chain cast, and the chain casters are trying to beat you by getting improvements. Meanwhile you're doing the same thing a different way, trying to make nonchaincasters the superior breed by preventing chain casters from being improved upon.<br>
<br>
Chain casting isn't for everyone, and I'll grant most the benefit of the doubt that they've tried it and just didn't like it.<br>
<br>
But there's always the nagging doubt in my mind when I see a fervent anti-chain-caster. Lazy. Afraid of change. Has never even tried chain casting pets or even cannipetting.<br>
<br>
To that portion of nonchainers who are just too lazy, sucky, or afraid of change, I have no sympathy.<br>
<br>
1) If you haven't tried chain casting, try it<br>
<br>
2) SOE will never balance mages purely around chain casting. But THAT DOESNT MEAN CHAIN CASTING CANT BE VIABLE. If you don't want to chain cast pets, YIPPEE SKIPPY FOR YOU. That doesn't mean you have to prevent the rest of us from doing it.<br>
<br>
3) Stop making up lame reasons for hating chain casting, such as  it's &quot;wasn't intended&quot; or it's &quot;hurting our class.&quot; You can just not like it, you don't have to come up with reasons, because the reasons you come up with will probably be fake and never convince anyone of anything.<br>
<br>
Immlazen, in the latter half of your post, you somehow twist everything around and blame it on my fellow chain casters. Simply put: WTF? I highly doubt that anything you refer to has more to do with chain casting pets than our ability to have the pet tank and shoot fireballs at the mob. <br>
<br>
I could say that pet hp weren't improved, because if the pet could tank any longer than it does, I'd be able to sustain chain nuking DPS long enough to kill a mob. However, if I made that statement, it'd be pretty cheesy, so maybe you can understand how cheesy your statement about chain casting hurting pet upgrades sounds to me.<br>
<br>
I dream of the day that nonchain casters and chaincasters of pets can live in harmony. But you nonchain casters sure are hostile nazis towards chaincasting of pets.<br>
<br>
Human beings are afraid of change, it's our nature. The irony is, change is the only thing we have to hope for. Change is the way we grow, change makes us stronger. Why, then, are we so afraid? <p>Happy trails.</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krilenspiritlink>Krilen Spiritlink</A> at: 11/22/02 6:47:27 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bgilles>bgilles</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#333333>(11/22/02 12:06:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=408.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: hmm</span><hr size=1> Krilen you are totaly wrong<br>
