Back in the day, I used to argue with my family over anything and everything just for sport. The general rule for more heated debates was that if any person were to insult any other person, no matter how subtley disguised the insult was, the insulter the loser. I think it's a very good rule for debates: the only time you really have to turn to insults is when you're at a loss for valid arguments to make. You may not be my family, but at this point, as far as I'm concerned, you lose. Frankly, age has nothing to do with anything, although if it did, you've certainly shown your maturity simply by making that statement.<br>
<br>
1) You're complaining that you can't solo like you used to. 2)You're complaining that the only ways to solo now are agro kiting and chain casting pets. 3) You're somehow twisting words around in your head to blame pet's lack of the ability to tank on the mage's ability to chain cast pets. 4) Worse, you're blaming chain casting mages for all of your hardships. 5) You're saying that chain casting mages are nazis that only want improvements to chaining. 6) You want slow and you think it helps chain casters equally to non chain casters.<br>
<br>
1) Get over it and roll with the punches.<br>
2) Get over it and roll with the punches.<br>
3) Please stop that.<br>
4) Please stop that. These parties deserve no blame for anything, any more than any other party.<br>
5) The burnout spell suggested in the original post on this thread helps both chain casters and agro kiters(who may mess up and have to run ahead 6 seconds and make a new pet.)<br>
6) Slow, on the other hand, would only help you &amp; your style of play, you greedy little hypocrit. You obviously either know almost nothing about being a mage or are trying to trick casual readers who fit that description. Your statement that slow helps chainers and nonchainers equally is FALSE. Don't know why? Here's a hint... a chain caster who casts slow is an agro kiting beastlord. If you can't figure it out, get a beastlord friend, have him cast slow on a mob, and then cast a new pet, /pet get lost-ing the old pet to make way for the new one. Watch what happens. <br>
<br>
In conclusion: You blame chaincasting mages for asking for upgrades only to chain casting mages and leaving the rest behind. This however, is not true, as the suggested burnout+ds helps 2 facets of solo, agro kite and chain cast. The only suggestion that you, the supposed objective mage crusading for the good of _all_ mages, could come up with: Slow. Slow would help agro kiters, and people who like to have 1 pet and have him tank. However, before any improvements are made, people who like to have 1 pet and have him tank is not a solo category for the magician. And, slow helps chainers less than burnout+ds helps people who like to have 1 pet aand have him tank, as slow has absolutely 0 impact on chaining.<br>
<br>
Therefore, where burnout+ds covers 2/2 solo categories, slow merely creates a new one, but the ratio is 2/3. I'm going to have to ask that, in future suggestions for improvements, that you should suggest suggestions which cover a full 100% of mages instead of creating new categories. Please think of all mages instead of just spreading us thinner, thx.<br>
<br>
ps. mages are not the only class who solo much differently at low levels than high levels. In fact, very few casting classes, if any, solo the same way 1-50 as 50-60 as 60-65. Please stop saying that mages have to change when everyone else keeps their same strats. It simply isn't true. <p>Happy trails.</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32>Class Balance</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
